The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Devang to lead against TN
 BY A STAFF REPORTER  Calcutta: Devang Gandhi  will lead Bengal in the Ranji Trophy tie against Tamil Nadu  beginning in Thirunelveli on Sunday. Devang and Arindam  Das were called in absence of Rohan Gavaskar and Deep Dasgupta. While Deep has been picked for the Australia-bound national squad, Rohan has been named in the India A team to take on Sri Lanka A. Devang missed the last tie owing to family commitments.  Prasannas advice Erapalli Prasanna has called for the appointment of a full-time coach in the proposed spinners wing of the National Cricket Academy in Bangalore. In the spinners conclave that took place in the city on Thursday, Prasanna, S. Venkatraghavan, Bishan Singh Bedi and Sunil Gavaskar were present.  Copyright 
